ZH: 我每天早上都会排便。
EN: I have a bowel movement every morning.

ZH: 吃纤维丰富的食物可以帮助排便。
EN: Eating fiber-rich foods can help with bowel movements.

ZH: 如果排便不正常，可能需要就医。
EN: It may be necessary to see a doctor if your bowel movements are irregular.

ZH: 忽略排便问题可能会导致疾病。
EN: Ignoring bowel movement issues can lead to illness.

ZH: 有时候排便会变得频繁。
EN: Sometimes bowel movements can become more frequent.

ZH: 饮水不足可能会导致便秘。
EN: Not drinking enough water can lead to constipation.

ZH: 吃太多快餐可能会影响排便。
EN: Eating too much fast food may affect bowel movements.

ZH: 坐立不安也可能会造成排便困难。
EN: Being restless can also cause difficulty with bowel movements.

ZH: 懒散的生活方式可能会导致排便不顺。
EN: A sedentary lifestyle may lead to irregular bowel movements.

ZH: 长时间憋尿可能会影响排便。
EN: Holding in urine for extended periods of time can affect bowel movements.

ZH: 蔬菜水果对促进排便很有好处。
EN: Vegetables and fruits are beneficial for promoting bowel movements.

ZH: 缺乏运动可能会导致排便困难。
EN: Lack of exercise may result in difficulties with bowel movements.

ZH: 睡前喝杯热水有助于排便。
EN: Drinking a glass of warm water before bed can help with bowel movements.

ZH: 有些人每天只排便一次。
EN: Some people only have one bowel movement per day.

ZH: 排便应该是自然的生理反应。
EN: Bowel movements should be a natural physiological response.

ZH: 忽视排便问题可能会导致肠道疾病。
EN: Ignoring bowel movement issues can result in intestinal diseases.

ZH: 食用富含益生菌的食物有助促进排便。
EN: Consuming probiotic-rich foods can help promote bowel movements.

ZH: 长时间拉肚子可能会导致排便过度。
EN: Having diarrhea for an extended period of time can result in excessive bowel movements.

ZH: 坚持定时排便对健康很重要。
EN: Maintaining a regular schedule for bowel movements is important for health.

ZH: 吃太多含糖食物可能会影响排便。
EN: Eating too many sugary foods may affect bowel movements.
